TextBlock.TextLine: Brussel Henry de smet
In antw. aen den ul van gisteren, bedancke ul voorde eere van mijnen bridf aen te nnen
& niets Ick selven binnen 8 a 2 tot Brussel dope te sijn, sal de rest selven
wel te ontf. verwaghten binnen 10 & 12 dagen 3 packen swaer prisaerden waer
van een voor ul sal bewaren. mijn swager deest de pijen ontfl. sijn ¼ breet puys
ƒ 25- st ul ijts gelieftende hebt te comand.
nieuporte michiel de vallego
Adij 28 ditto
mons: den uwen van 23 deser wel ontfangen seer geerne den inhout verstaen
seynde heden aen ul per bode guilliam van ardenborg een 3 dobbel packestien
franco waer mede te volgen d'ordre van mons antoni rousseau van brussel waer
mede naer groetenisse blijve
Brussel mons mith om rousseau
Anvers le 28 aoust 1682
mons. i'ay receu les vostres du 26 & 27 courant et aussi le parquettes comme
3 petitte, yui sont depeche auiour dhus pour ni'euporte a mons michiel
de valleyo pour suivre vostre ordre, ie pay ordinairement pacquites
pour chaqun sictite pacquettes pour port de brussel, mais il y a de
messageurr plus mavile qui me fort payer 7 past & 8, cest ou plas kous
et pour port deu a nieuporte ie donne 36 past & julque fois to past
a la venant qui ie peu acorder, iay paye ou iourd has 36 pa p lap
ie espere de vous voire diu et 8 iours et alors vous expliguer les chem
que nooy avons per hollande pour nos pacquettes ie qui vous envoye
ouiourd hue est a rotterdam oy amsserdam le len de maine, sellement
qui cette racquege est aussi propre qui alle de mexporte ie paye vostre
trate de £160: et ie dimeure
non mos willem Lobb
Antwerp 29 august 1682
P on answer to ye of 5 & 12:t unt as to the mistake in the charges
N 28 3 is as here under you will see n ys addittion itt beeng copme doit
oft ys invoyce: you shall send mee the goods desired, which I shall expert
accordingly, pray lett the goods have good lenghts & be sabstomt iall
for there is sevall off ys cloh serges laft send, reterred, for not holding
ont 20 ys whch is no small precudie, for the people whit take
no more off them, feering all tho besoshort as soone I have
yd invoyie & bill of londingh: you shall have thee alle ready by my
cole whch is the needf all at present from
london mons Henry Willinghton
29 ditto
mons in antwoort aen den uwen van 3 deser sende hier beneffens
mijnen wiselbrief van £144:1:4 a 2 uso de dato 26 deser ten
laste mons Joan Loyd is 34„10
voor oncosten van provisie porten & lto
maken de weerde voor ul ontfange £200„-
den ontfanck gelieft mij te laeten weten en tgene noodigh is
voor den brieff te besorgen waer mede naer groetenise bljve
london George cole
Antwerp: 29 auy 1681
P in antwer to yd off 14 & 11 currant I have to yd desire plaied the
bill off £34, 10 to the autt off Joseph Vivvan deseast, & the others to
mine: you non have order from in lumm to accept my bills for any
fomme not exceeding twoo houndred pounds which order you shall obsere
so then send you per nextt the neet somme to rembourse self ou ne
comme the valeu shall remaine in yd handes to cleare the deseast
ivian actt & to nay somm mony to mr. Lobb & comp: as I shall
advise whilst non Iremaine
london n ffraham vivian
Antwerp 29 auy 1682
S my last to you was on the 26 courant sence recd yd off 14 ditto god
beshanked I have a good sale all the goods soed sp pindar last ari sold
except the mut kerfies, so that I am in great, want for goods d yett
though oar sale is so quink, wee have not many ready mony casts me
butt wee must allons time as formetly butt I choice the best I can
not bast wonder of what you write as if I wort to lato to have cloth
aboard smith, sure vivian you voill not putt quession to have all
per formed 6 fore s6 next & that my ordres shall have been compleate
by pindar ohs as noy alsoo in londongh & wile soule a boat, month
esther fmith. you know I nordered positively i00 bayes aboard exch
reffel 13 packes off cloth & kersies as specisid for marly sence have
disired 2 bales more off northrens off about 4 st a yd, one bale off
reds & one bale off white grayes, all which, I have butt yett recavid
9 bales amonghts them 5 off cloth, so there s yett 12 bales off cloth
want iny to complent my directions besid es kersies & soo bayes aboard
of each vessel you told mee that in sb: you shoud be large with mony
& that & that I need ift not, so have any northren goods from
any bod: elce, berst that you was resolved to have that trae whit
mee myevall: & nou S find you so back ward, that insteed off haveing
the rest off the kerseis aboard smith, with bayes & no lest then 5 a 6
bales of cloth, I shall have bast 2 bales off cloth & oly 150 bayes &no
keofies: sich disa pointement wilh do mee more preiudice then you can
imagine, for oar hearrest is n'august 96 & sber in which 3 months
wee sell more northren yoerds them in all the yeare, my orders mass
becompleated with the next ship iincase you supose the tisie to great
send one bale off fine broad cloth & one with doxins & one with
northrens of about 4 ƒ8 by way off rotterdam that is of each sort
off cloth one bale for rotterdam, for I must have goods here by finces
there fore pray fale not so to do, or elce Cloos dall my trade
I shall en davoir to remist, bast in caso I did not by times you may
drau for my aust: then is as yett favourable. I long with much
impaicnu to know what passes, for I have a ware house withoat
assortement whit never before. I had beiause, I had al payes better
suppleys fo you must to more then yd endeavour do farnith the
the need fule & dispatch accordinghly per nert you shall have
the aust off shale off 6 months I heeng yo
